Here's the complete implementation:

**Configure request size limits** in `Program.cs`:

```csharp
// Allow up to ~11 MB at the server level so your 10 MB check runs
// before Kestrel rejects the request.
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 11 * 1024 * 1024);
```

**Add the endpoint** (after `var app = builder.Build();`):

```csharp
app.MapPost("/upload", async (IFormFile file) =>
{
    const long maxSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10 MB
    string[] allowed = [".jpg", ".jpeg", ".png"];

    var ext = Path.GetExtension(file.FileName).ToLowerInvariant();

    if (!allowed.Contains(ext))
        return Results.BadRequest("Only JPEG and PNG files are allowed.");

    if (file.Length > maxSize)
        return Results.BadRequest("File size must not exceed 10 MB.");

    var uploadsDir = Path.Combine(app.Environment.ContentRootPath, "uploads");
    Directory.CreateDirectory(uploadsDir);

    // Avoid path traversal and collisions with a random name
    var safeName = $"{Guid.NewGuid()}{ext}";
    var path = Path.Combine(uploadsDir, safeName);

    await using var stream = File.Create(path);
    await file.CopyToAsync(stream);

    return Results.Ok(new { fileName = safeName });
})
.DisableAntiforgery()          // file uploads from API clients won't have the token
.RequestSizeLimit(11_534_336); // per-endpoint override (~11 MB)
```

Key points:

- **`.DisableAntiforgery()`** — since you have `UseAntiforgery()` globally, API callers (Fetch, curl, mobile) won't send an antiforgery token. Remove this if uploads come exclusively from Razor/Blazor forms that include the token.
- **`RequestSizeLimit`** — sets the per-endpoint cap slightly above 10 MB so your own validation message is returned instead of a generic 413.
- **`Guid.NewGuid()`** — prevents path-traversal attacks and filename collisions; the original filename is never used on disk.
- **`Directory.CreateDirectory`** — is a no-op if the folder already exists.

If your uploads come from an HTML form that *does* include the antiforgery token, drop `.DisableAntiforgery()` and keep the global middleware.
